# Case C: DEI Interactive Timeline

## Client
Dr. McCarter, DEI Office

## Problem
Pomfret's DEI history is fragmented across informal sources and not accessible to the community.

## Goal
Build an interactive digital experience showcasing Pomfret's DEI history, to be integrated into the main Pomfret School website under the DEI section.

## Tech Stack
Next.js 14, Sanity CMS, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion

## Team
Developers: Zahir Williams, Keke Li
Club Lead: Cayden Auyang

## Onboarding & Workflow
All git, branching, pull request, commit message, and merge conflict guidance lives in [`../../docs/developer-onboarding.md`](../../docs/developer-onboarding.md). Reference it before answering workflow questions. Do not duplicate its content here.

## Working Rules
- This folder is scoped to Case C only. Do not modify files outside projects/case-c-dei-timeline/ unless explicitly asked.
- Do not commit secrets, API keys, or credentials. Use .env files and add them to .gitignore.
- Follow the club branch naming convention: case-c/short-description (lowercase, hyphens).
- Never push directly to main. All changes go through a Pull Request with at least 1 approval.
- When writing code, prefer clarity over cleverness. These developers are high school students learning collaborative coding.
- If you generate code the developer cannot explain, flag it and summarize what it does in plain English.

## Definition of Done (Phase 1)
Prototype approved by Dr. McCarter, Sanity CMS connected (no more hardcoded demo data), code hygiene issues resolved (README restored, .env.example added, .claude/ added to .gitignore, 'Career Span' label renamed to 'Year Range', lockfile committed), ready to hand to Communications for integration.
